FBIS3-22629 "jptep007___94039" JPRS-TEP-94-004 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Epidemiology 11 March 1994 LATIN AMERICA REGIONAL AFFAIRS Colombia To Buy Cuban Vaccines FL1302200694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 12 Feb 94 FL1302200694 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Cuban and Colombian health experts are currently analyzing, in Bogota, the agreements for Cuban-Colombian technical cooperation in health matters. These agreements, which were signed in January during the visit to Havana of Colombian Public Health Minister Juan Luis Londono, have to do with vaccination, monitoring, epidemiology, strengthening the network of laboratories, primary health care, medicines, tropical diseases, hospital equipment maintenance, and the training of human resources. The work done by Cuba in vaccines against meningitis and hepatitis-B is noted in an official communique. Important medicines of that kind will be purchased by Colombia. There is also progess as regards the 5-year vaccination program and the tropical disease program. The Cuban delegation will be in Colombia until 17 February.
